                   "message":  "SAVE-SOURCE-DISPLAY-NAME: SaveSource::display_name() — project title/status show folder name, not literal .rge-project\n\nAdds SaveSource::display_name() -\u003e Option\u003c\u0026str\u003e: a Scene shows its .rge-scene\nfile name (unchanged); a Project shows its parent FOLDER name (e.g. \"my-game\")\ninstead of the literal \".rge-project\", falling back to the file name when the\npath has no parent directory. Pure-path — no manifest read (editor-shell stays\nloader-free), no SaveSource shape change.\n\nRouted the window title (editor_window_title now takes the resolved Option\u003c\u0026str\u003e\ndisplay name) and the save-status snapshot (scene_file_name) through\ndisplay_name(). Updated the now-false \"literal .rge-project\" /\n\"pre-extracted via Path::file_name\" title/status prose (editor-shell +\neditor-state docs); the accurate path/format/open-routing \"literal .rge-project\"\nreferences stay.\n\n5 files (editor-shell save_source/mod/window_title/tests + editor-state doc),\n0 Cargo.toml, no binary change. +6 tests (display_name unit cases incl. the\nno-parent fallback + Scene/Project status-snapshot integration).\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints. (A shared-target cache-poisoning\nfalse-negative from the just-pruned #274 worktree was cleared via cargo clean -p\non 8 unrelated baked-asset crates; re-gate green.)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
